## Week 3 — Day 4 | FastAPI /predict Endpoint

```bash
# Install dependencies
bash setup.sh

# Start backend (from Backend/ directory)
cd Backend
uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# Test normal reading
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"cpu_percent": 0.13, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T21:50:00"}'

# Prime rolling window then test spike
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 0.13, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T21:40:00"}'
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 0.13, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T21:45:00"}'
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 0.13, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T21:50:00"}'
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 0.13, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T21:55:00"}'
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 2.344, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T22:05:00"}'

# Commit endpoint
git add backend/app/services/ml_model.py backend/app/routes/prediction.py backend/app/schemas/metric_schema.py
git commit -m "feat: /predict endpoint live, rolling window context added, anomaly detection working end-to-end"
git push
```

**Result:** Normal readings return `"anomaly": false`. Spike after primed baseline returns `"anomaly": true, "message": "ANOMALY DETECTED"`. Rolling window of 12 readings replicates training context at inference time.

