## Week 4 — Day 1 | Dockerise Backend

```bash
# Build Docker image
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml build

# Start containers
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml up --build

# Verify containers running
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml ps

# Test predict endpoint inside container (prime first)
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 0.13, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T21:40:00"}'
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"cpu_percent": 2.344, "timestamp": "2014-02-26T22:05:00"}'

# Stop containers
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml down

# Commit
git add Backend/Dockerfile docker/docker-compose.yml Backend/requirements.txt
git commit -m "feat: backend and postgres containerised, anomaly detection verified inside Docker"
git push
```

**Result:** Backend and PostgreSQL running as Docker containers. Model path resolved via `MODEL_PATH` environment variable — works in Docker, CI, and local environments.

