## Week 4 — Day 3 | CI/CD Pipeline — GitHub Actions

```bash
# Install linting tools
pip install flake8 autopep8

# Run linter locally
flake8 Backend/app/ ml/ --max-line-length=120 --exclude=__pycache__,ml/NAB --ignore=E501,W503

# Auto-fix formatting
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive Backend/app/main.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive Backend/app/routes/prediction.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive Backend/app/schemas/metric_schema.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive Backend/app/services/ml_model.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive ml/evaluate_model.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive ml/fetch_metrics.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive ml/prepare_dataset.py
autopep8 --in-place --aggressive ml/train_model.py

# Verify clean
flake8 Backend/app/ ml/ --max-line-length=120 --exclude=__pycache__,ml/NAB --ignore=E501,W503

# Commit pipeline
git add .github/workflows/ci-cd.yml
git commit -m "feat: GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline added, all lint errors fixed"
git push
```

**Pipeline jobs (`.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml`):**
1. **Lint Python** — flake8 on Backend/app/ and ml/
2. **Build Docker Image** — builds backend image via docker compose
3. **Test Predict Endpoint** — trains model, starts backend, primes window, asserts normal=false and spike=true

**Result:** All three jobs green. Pipeline triggers on every push to main. Anomaly detection verified automatically in CI on each commit.

